##Dictation | we stayed up all night for 1,800 hospital breakfasts

Micro-signal Xinminzhoukan

Function description, depth and angle —— this is what we can do.

In addition to the handling and delivery of dishes, I am responsible for preparing different recipes for different groups of people in different hospitals. For example, the nurse community needs to add anti-fatigue ingredients, the panel's menu can be slightly bland, and the construction workers'menu needs to be heavy in oil.

The stones are still there

By Liu Chaohui

Between last night and today, my brothers and I stayed up all night making 1,800 emergency breakfasts. Now I still can not sleep, a new day, we still have heavy duty, Wuhan, there are many hospitals and volunteers waiting for us to deliver lunch and dinner. What we've been doing every day since the city was shut down, is getting hot, fresh food to the people on the front lines.

My name is Shi Zai Yu, is a self-selected Chinese food chain brand "Mr. Rice" in Wuhan's regional executive chef. In Wuhan we have more than 160 stores, the epidemic has been basically closed, now only a dozen have been allowed to special business. With just over a dozen restaurants, we serve tens of thousands of meals a day to hospitals and quarantine sites in Wuhan.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Shi jae-jae delivers boxed meals for medical staff

10,000 servings of rice delivered to 8:00 p.m

On the eve of the Lunar New Year, news spread on the Internet that medical staff in Wuhan were having trouble eating. When we learned at our headquarters in Chongqing, we immediately pulled 4,000 self-heating rice from the warehouse and recalled some of the workers who had been on vacation, on the first day of the Lunar New Year, 6,000 self-heating rice dishes were produced, and 10,000 were shipped to Wuhan. The transportation was not smooth because of the traffic control. Our colleague through sends the friend circle to seek help, finally under the warm-hearted citizen's help, only then found the related department to complete the formalities.

Through the Hubei Charity Association and other departments to coordinate and help, on the third day of the Lunar New Year, I and five colleagues, are unloading and loading, more than 4000 self-heating boxed meals sent to the central South Hospital of Wuhan University. The rest will be sent to the Health Care Commission of Wuchang District, which will distribute them to all the major hospitals in Wuchang District. All Day Long, until eight o'clock in the evening, everyone was exhausted, but the heart is still very happy. The people who received them thanked us. I said it was the company that should be thanked. We are just working on behalf of the company on the front line.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Self-heating rice arrived at central South Hospital

I also know that 10,000 servings of rice is a drop in the bucket for hospitals in Wuhan. If we want to help the people who are fighting on the front lines, we have to do everything we can, with our resources, to give them more support. It just so happens that the Culinary Association sent out a notice for volunteers, and I was the first member of the Association to sign up. Then I carried on the initiative in the Wechat Group of companies, many people are my apprentices, everyone signed up very enthusiastically. In the end, too many people signed up, even had to pull some strings.

Delivering meals to the Vulcan Mountain construction site

Because a lot of catering enterprises are closed, Wuhan hospitals, isolated point of the hotel, the demand for food and beverage is really great. We take the initiative with the Culinary Association, the major hospitals, the Commerce Bureau and other docking, to understand their needs, my wechat has recently built nearly 30 groups, are the needs of docking and coordination. And there are also teams of volunteers, who are transporting patients and medical staff, and supplies, that are contributing to the fight against the epidemic, and we're also providing them with free boxed meals.

These groups are very busy every day, each unit will continue to send the order of the day, and then I have to coordinate the implementation of the order to a dozen stores, almost no spare. These numbers are increasing as medical teams arrive from all over the country. A hospital wechat group inside, a doctor posted a sentence: I finally eat rice, we have not eaten rice for more than 10 days. We read the message, happy that the paramedics were getting the free meals we had given them, and our noses were a little sore.

Fire Mountain Hospital construction, heard that the construction task of the three bureau of the food supply is not, we took the initiative to contact the three bureau of the construction. The other side began to say to pay, I said you are in the fight against the epidemic to contribute, we can provide you with free lunch box, rare opportunity, the other side also quite embarrassed. So we delivered lunch and dinner to the construction site every day, more than 700, to the Vulcan Mountain Hospital completed, six days in a total of more than 4,000 free box lunch.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Workers at the Vulcan Mountain construction site had hot boxed meals

Two meat and a vegetarian lunch box to the fire God mountain construction site, the workers are satisfied with the taste of the dishes, but many people said that less food. I realized that the construction workers'physical exertion was so great that they could not be satisfied with the standard box meals, so we not only increased the quantity of meals, but also increased the oil in the dishes, so that the workers and the cooks could eat well.

1,800 breakfasts are suddenly in demand

Today, we serve about 10,000 free boxed meals a day, including lunch and dinner, nearly half of which go to hospitals. Changhang Hospital, Union Hospital, Lung Hospital, the Fourth Hospital... There are seven or eight hospitals are in charge of our delivery. Since this time, the medical staff to our free food delivery operations have expressed their gratitude, can be recognized by them, our hearts are hot and warm.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Wechat message of thanks from health care workers

On the evening of February 18, my wechat group suddenly sent a message that the Tongji Hospital's Zhongfa new district needed 1,800 breakfasts. The director of the docking station said that their doctor and nurse had been eating milk and bread for breakfast and wanted a warm breakfast. It was nearly 10:40 at night, and I was a little flustered. Before we sent a total of breakfast every day is more than a thousand, and Tongji Hospital this is a number of hospitals.

I immediately called the store manager in the group meeting for emergency deployment, ask which store can take orders. This suddenly under the single so big, and more urgent, with single group, shop owners see a bit afraid. My thought is, this list we must take down, must satisfy the doctors and nurses this wish.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
After a busy night of preparation, we finally got all the ingredients for the 1,800 breakfasts ready, and then the urgent production, and then the nine people went to the stores and packed the breakfasts into incubators as fast as they could, in addition to coordinating vehicles, contact the hospital to get out of the city pass. We have to get breakfast to the doctors and nurses before 7:00, because when they go to work after 7:00, they won't be able to eat breakfast. At 6:00 am on February 19, we set off for Tongji Hospital in Caidian Zhongfa new town, 40 km away, and finally delivered breakfast to the hospital at 6:40 am.

I was up all night working with a group of colleagues for 1,800 breakfasts. The breakfast consists of two eggs, a cup of soy milk, a roasted wheat, two steamed dumplings and a steamed bun, which hopefully will help doctors, nurses and experts provide their own immunity.

Tangyuan on Lantern Festival makes nurses cry

In addition to the handling and delivery of dishes, I am responsible for preparing different recipes for different groups of people in different hospitals. For example, the nurse community needs to add anti-fatigue ingredients, the panel's menu can be slightly bland, and the construction workers'menu needs to be heavy in oil. Although our raw material procurement is basically still able to meet demand, but in times of emergency, it is not so rich, so I have to find a way to turn over a pattern on the dishes.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
For example, there have been a lot of ducks in the ingredients recently, so we changed our taste. Today it's braised duck, tomorrow it's King Roast Duck, and the day after that it's stewed duck leg. Not In the same way. People who eat them feel differently, and they don't lose their appetite. Our Menu won't be repeated for a week. At this time, we are not in a good mood, we hope that from the Diet to make everyone happy, appetite a little better, increase the resistance to the virus.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The Cook is nervous about preparing the meal

Some hospitals have halal and vegetarian requests coming in, and we can meet their needs. A custom-made halal meal consisting mainly of beef, mutton and fish, individually wrapped. A vegetarian diet is vegetables, potatoes, carrots and the like.

On the Lantern Festival day, we specially sent 7,000 Tangyuan to the box lunch, which also contains medlar and egg flower. When the food was delivered, I saw several nurses with tears in their eyes when they saw the dumpling. During the Lantern Festival, these medical staff can not be reunited with their families. We are sending this dumpling to give them more warm care as much as we can.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Chinanews.com report video

My son called me a hero

We now have more than 100 employees working in Wuhan. Many people have to get up at 4:00 every morning, 5:00 on duty, washing dishes washing rice, processing cooking, packaging box lunch... I also often visit the shop, sometimes personally cook help them cook, send box lunch. Every day is to be busy until after eight o'clock in the evening, I can drag tired body back to the dormitory to rest, the brothers are also hard. Because the buses were all stopped and the private cars wouldn't move, a colleague had to ride a shared bike for an hour and a half to get to and from work. The close management of the small area, also brought some inconvenience to our work. A few days ago, there are eight people in a shop, there are five gated communities can not come out, only three people completed the task of the day. Fortunately, after these two days and the coordination of communication with the community, our staff can be smooth on duty.

Although very tired, but our enthusiasm is very high, the spirit is very full. In a group, everyone likes each other and is a team player. We are all aware that we are doing a very meaningful thing, we are contributing to society. We don't Cook like the front-line medical staff, we are a bit tired, but compared to their danger and hard work, it is nothing. But when the outbreak is over, the hard work of these employees will be recognized.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Seok jae-yojae carries lunch boxes

I was going to go home for the Spring Festival. There's a lot going on at home. My father was seriously ill in hospital, and my 8 year old son was waiting for me at home in Chongqing. Being locked up in Wuhan, said not anxious is false, can not go back to accompany the family is also very sorry, feel very sorry for them. But think, now that I'm here, I might as well do something about it.

My family has shown me understanding and support. Every day, I would and my father and family video call, they are also very concerned about my body, told me to pay attention to safety. My father told me that if he had been young, he would have made the same choice I did.

Not long ago, Changjiang daily interviewed me and reported on our team. When I told the family, my son gave me a thumbs-up in the video and said, "Daddy's a big hero! " I felt a sense of relief and pride in my heart. My son's words inspired me. I must set an example for him.

I'm not a hero. The people on the front lines are heroes. With these heroes, Wuhan will surely pull through.
